main event: The witness observed several bright silver objects that did not appear to be airplanes, helicopters or birds in Gloucester, Massachusetts on April 23, 1963.
interesting points: The objects were described as bright silver in color and glowing.
The objects followed an erratic course that was difficult for the witness to describe.
The witness was unsure of what the objects were, but was certain they were not any normal aircraft.
The witness described the objects as appearing to be smaller circular objects proceeding to a central disc.
